    "discriminators": [
     "Dripping, flowing, gushing, spurting — this is LIQUID, and liquid is liquid. UCS says as much itself: 'Likely some overlap with LIQUID & MUD, but this for particularly gory versions.' Gore-ness is a NARRATIVE property, not a spectral one.",
     "Physically indistinguishable from LIQUID & MUD-MOVEMENT and WATER-DRIP / WATER-FLOW. The only lean is viscosity: blood is thicker than water, so expect a slightly lower centroid and heavier, lower-crest globby onsets than a clean water drip.",
     "Against GORE-OOZE: dripping and flowing (this) vs slow viscous seeping and burbling (OOZE). No boundary. Against GORE-SPLAT: a splat is an IMPACT; this is a flow."
    ],
