    "discriminators": [
     "Flesh sizzling: a sustained, stationary, HF-dominated stochastic hiss with a very LOW crest factor. Morphologically it is the exact opposite of every impact in GORE — it does not spike, it sustains. Separable from the rest of the category on centroid, crest and sustain alone.",
     "Against FIRE-SIZZLE, per the UCS note ('possible overlap with FIRE-SIZZLING, but this more exaggerated for flesh burning'): identical physics. The stated difference is EXAGGERATION — a gore sizzle is hotter, wetter and more aggressive, with more spitting transients riding on the hiss. That is a production choice, not a measurement, and text must carry it.",
