    "discriminators": [
     "Tearing and ripping: a SUSTAINED, unstable, high-flux friction gesture, not an impact. It has duration and a churning spectrum where a splat has neither. Low crest, high spectral_flux, real sustain_ratio — that trio is the morphology, and it cleanly separates FLESH from SPLAT, SQUISH, STAB and BONE, all of which are impulsive.",
